                                                                                      BRANCHING IN GIT
								----------------------------------------------------------------

       This is a feature of git which allows team members to create code related to various functionalities on different branches and later merge them with the "master" branch."master" branch is the default bra

       nch of git. Branching helps us to create the code in an uncluttered way

       COMMANDS
    ----------------

    git branch
    ------------

    This command is used to see the list of all local branches

    git branch -a
    ---------------

    This command is used to see the list of all loacl branches (local and remote )

    git branch branch_name
    ------------------------

    this command is used to create a new branch

    git checkout branch_name
    --------------------------

    This command is used to move into a specific branch

    git checkout -b branch_name
    ----------------------------

    This command is used to create a branch and also move into it

    git merge branch_name
    ---------------------------

    This command is used to merge a branch

    git branch -d branch-name
    ----------------------------

    This command is used to delete a branch that is already merged.this is called as soft delete

    git branch -D branch_name
    ----------------------------

    This command is used to deleted a branch that is not merged .This is called as hard delete

    "note"
    ------------
    Whenever the branch is created the entire commit history of the parent branch will be copied into the new branch

    "note"
    -----------

    Irrespective of which branch a file is created or modified git only check from which branch it is commited and the file belongs to the commited brench only
